<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - REAR OIL SEAL AND WEAR SLEEVE - REAR OIL SEAL REMOVAL
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="2">
        <title>REAR OIL SEAL REMOVAL</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Use this method if the rear oil seal removal tool is not available.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Punch two holes into the rear oil seal and insert two sheet metal screws (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050714">7.14</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1050713" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg3062" filename="../figeg3/EG3062.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.13.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Rear Oil Seal Gasket</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Rear Oil Seal Carrier</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Installation Tool</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1050714" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg3066" filename="../figeg3/EG3066.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.14.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Oil Seal Carrier</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Crankcase</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Crankshaft</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Punch</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. Hammer</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using a small pry bar, alternately pry on each screw to remove rear oil seal from the
                carrier (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e105_137.xml" xrefid="ef1050715">7.15</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Discard old oil seal.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>It is not necessary to remove the flywheel housing if all that is required is to replace the
                        crankshaft rear oil seal or wear sleeve.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
